Package: dsRadiomics
Type: Package
Title: DataSHIELD Radiomics Feature Extraction and Segmentation
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("David", "Sarrat González", role = c("aut", "cre"), email = "david.sarrat@isglobal.org"),
    person("Juan R", "González", role = "aut", email = "juanr.gonzalez@isglobal.org"))
Description: Server-side DataSHIELD package for radiomics feature extraction
    and image segmentation. Provides allowlisted artifact runners for
    PyRadiomics, TotalSegmentator, nnU-Net v2, and MONAI bundles. Manages
    segmentation model registry, radiomics profiles, and publishes derived
    assets (feature tables, mask roots) into the dsImaging asset catalog.
    Built on top of dsJobs for durable execution and dsImaging for asset
    management.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    jsonlite,
    digest,
    processx,
    utils
Suggests:
    dsJobs,
    dsImaging,
    yaml,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    withr
Config/testthat/edition: 3
